The **Jacobian** of $\mathbf{f}(t, \mathbf{y})$ with respect to $\mathbf{y}$ is:
\[
J = \frac{\partial \mathbf{f}}{\partial \mathbf{y}} = 
\begin{pmatrix}
\frac{\partial f_1}{\partial y_1} & \cdots & \frac{\partial f_1}{\partial y_m} \\
\vdots & \ddots & \vdots \\
\frac{\partial f_m}{\partial y_1} & \cdots & \frac{\partial f_m}{\partial y_m}
\end{pmatrix}
\]
